data.current_description: Exports a copy of all or a subset of entities from Google Cloud Datastore to another storage system, such as Google Cloud Storage. Recent updates to entities may not be reflected in the export. The export occurs in the background and its progress can be monitored and managed via the Operation resource that is created. The output of an export may only be used once the associated operation is done. If an export operation is cancelled before completion it may leave partial data behind in Google Cloud Storage.
data.summary_suggestion: Export Datastore entities to external storage
data.description_suggestion: Exports all or a filtered subset of entities from Google Cloud Datastore to an external storage system (e.g., Google Cloud Storage). The operation executes asynchronously and returns a long-running Operation resource for progress monitoring. Exported data reflects the state at export initiation; recent updates may not be included. The export output is only valid after the operation completes successfully. Cancelling an in-progress export may result in partial data in the destination storage. Requires the projectId parameter and an ExportEntitiesRequest specifying the target storage location and optional entity filters (kinds and namespaces).

data.current_description: Imports entities into Google Cloud Datastore. Existing entities with the same key are overwritten. The import occurs in the background and its progress can be monitored and managed via the Operation resource that is created. If an ImportEntities operation is cancelled, it is possible that a subset of the data has already been imported to Cloud Datastore.
data.summary_suggestion: Import entities into Google Cloud Datastore
data.description_suggestion: Imports entities from an external source into Google Cloud Datastore. Entities with matching keys are overwritten; no merge or conflict resolution occurs. The operation executes asynchronously and returns a long-running Operation resource for progress monitoring and management. Cancelling an in-progress import may result in partial data already persisted to Datastore. Requires the projectId parameter and an ImportEntitiesRequest specifying the source location and optional entity filters (kinds and namespaces). Verify source data integrity before import as partial imports cannot be easily rolled back.
